### **Self-Closing (Void) HTML Tags**

In HTML, **void elements** are self-closing tags that do not require a closing tag. They are **not** meant to contain any content. Importantly, **do not** include a trailing slash (`/`) in the opening tag.

#### **Common Void HTML Tags:**

1. **`<img>`**
   ```html
   <img src="images/profile.webp" alt="Profile Picture" width="210" loading="lazy">
   ```

2. **`<br>`**
   ```html
   <p>Line one.<br>Line two.</p>
   ```

3. **`<hr>`**
   ```html
   <hr>
   ```

4. **`<input>`**
   ```html
   <input type="text" name="username" placeholder="Enter your username">
   ```

5. **`<meta>`**
   ```html
   <meta charset="UTF-8">
   ```

6. **`<link>`**
   ```html
   <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles/index.css">
   ```

7. **`<area>`**
   ```html
   <map name="example-map">
       <area shape="rect" coords="34,44,270,350" href="sun.htm" alt="Sun">
   </map>
   ```

8. **`<base>`**
   ```html
   <base href="https://www.example.com/">
   ```

9. **`<col>`**
   ```html
   <table>
       <colgroup>
           <col span="2" style="background-color:yellow">
           <col style="background-color:blue">
       </colgroup>
       ...
   </table>
   ```

10. **`<embed>`**
    ```html
    <embed src="music.mp3" type="audio/mpeg">
    ```

11. **`<source>`**
    ```html
    <video controls>
        <source src="movie.mp4" type="video/mp4">
        Your browser does not support the video tag.
    </video>
    ```

12. **`<track>`**
    ```html
    <video controls>
        <source src="movie.mp4" type="video/mp4">
        <track kind="captions" src="captions_en.vtt" srclang="en" label="English">
    </video>
    ```

13. **`<wbr>`**
    ```html
    <p>Supercalifragilisticexpialidocious<wbr>is a long word.</p>
    ```

#### **Key Points:**

- **Do Not Use a Closing Slash:** In HTML5, it is **not necessary** to include a trailing slash in void elements. Simply use the tag without a closing tag or slash.
  
  **Correct:**
  ```html
  <img src="image.jpg" alt="Description">
  ```

  **Incorrect:**
  ```html
  <img src="image.jpg" alt="Description" />
  ```

- **No Content Inside Void Elements:** These tags should not wrap around any content. They stand alone in the HTML structure.

By adhering to these guidelines, you can ensure your HTML is both semantically correct and free from unnecessary syntax that might lead to validation errors or unintended behavior.




### **Definitions of HTML Elements and Attributes in the Snippet**

1. **`<section>` Tag**
   - **Definition:** A semantic HTML element used to group related content together within a webpage.
   - **Usage in Snippet:** 
     ```html
     <section class="temple highlight">
     ```
     This `<section>` wraps content related to the "Salt Lake Temple," indicating a distinct section of the page.

2. **`class` Attribute**
   - **Definition:** An HTML attribute that assigns one or more class names to an element. These classes are used for applying CSS styles or targeting elements with JavaScript.
   - **Usage in Snippet:** 
     ```html
     <section class="temple highlight">
     ```
     The `class` attribute here assigns two classes, `temple` and `highlight`, to the `<section>` element.

3. **`highlight`**
   - **Definition:** A class name assigned to an HTML element via the `class` attribute. It typically corresponds to specific CSS styles that visually distinguish the element.
   - **Usage in Snippet:** 
     ```html
     <section class="temple highlight">
     ```
     The `highlight` class likely applies special styling to emphasize the section, such as a different background color or border.

4. **`</>` (Closing Tag)**
   - **Definition:** Denotes the end of an HTML element. Every opening tag (e.g., `<section>`) should have a corresponding closing tag (e.g., `</section>`) unless it's a void element.
   - **Usage in Snippet:** 
     ```html
     </section>
     ```
     This closing tag signifies the end of the `<section>` element.

5. **`<h3>` Tag**
   - **Definition:** A heading tag in HTML representing a level 3 heading. Headings help structure the content hierarchically.
   - **Usage in Snippet:** 
     ```html
     <h3>Salt Lake Temple</h3>
     ```
     The `<h3>` tag is used here to title the section about the "Salt Lake Temple."

6. **Salt Lake Temple**
   - **Definition:** The text content within the `<h3>` tags. It serves as the heading for the section, providing a title or label.
   - **Usage in Snippet:** 
     ```html
     <h3>Salt Lake Temple</h3>
     ```
     "Salt Lake Temple" is the name of the landmark being described in this section.

