```html
<section class="temple highlight">
  <h3>Salt Lake Temple</h3>
  <p>The Salt Lake Temple is a landmark and symbol for The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints.</p>
  <p>The purpose of this temple and all other Latter-day Saint temples is to help all of God’s children come closer to Jesus Christ.</p>
</section>
```

- **`<section>`:** Groups the content related to the Salt Lake Temple.
- **`class="temple highlight"`:** Applies CSS styles from both `temple` and `highlight` classes.
- **`<h3>`:** Provides a subheading titled "Salt Lake Temple."
- **`</section>`:** Closes the section.

---

### **Additional Notes**

- **Semantic HTML:** Using semantic tags like `<section>` and `<h3>` improves the accessibility and SEO of your webpage.
- **CSS Styling:** The classes `temple` and `highlight` should be defined in your CSS files (`index.css` or `index-small.css`) to apply desired styles.
- **Avoiding Closing Slashes in Void Elements:** Remember that self-closing tags (e.g., `<br>`, `<img>`) do not require a closing slash in HTML5.

